From cdaffad35ead8e4ddc238fa43c783d9e07fa9f7b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Louis Clinckx <clinckx.louis@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 17:12:24 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 24/24] HID: hid-lenovo-go: reject non-USB devices in probe

hid_lenovo_go binds via HID_USB_DEVICE() id table entries and assumes
hdev->dev.parent is a struct usb_interface. The driver calls
get_endpoint_address() from .probe (line 2443), .raw_event (line 663)
and .remove (line 2460), which does:

    intf = to_usb_interface(hdev->dev.parent);
    if (!intf)
        return -ENODEV;
    ep = intf->cur_altsetting->endpoint;

to_usb_interface() is container_of(); it never returns NULL when the
parent pointer is non-NULL, so the !intf check is dead code. The
->cur_altsetting dereference then reads out of bounds whenever the
parent is not actually a struct usb_interface.

This is reachable via /dev/uhid. uhid lets userspace set
hdev->bus = BUS_USB (drivers/hid/uhid.c:525) while
hdev->dev.parent points to uhid's misc device, not a usb_interface.
hid_match_id() succeeds on bus/vendor/product alone, so hid_go_probe
runs and dereferences the bogus container_of() result.

The sibling driver hid-lenovo-go-s.c has an identical shape (its
if (intf) guard is similarly dead) and is fixed in the same patch.

KASAN trace (HEAD 50897c955902, KASAN_INLINE, CONFIG_UHID=m,
CONFIG_HID_LENOVO_GO=m):

  BUG: KASAN: slab-out-of-bounds in hid_go_probe+0x3d3/0x410 [hid_lenovo_go]
  Read of size 8 at addr ffff8880092b4f90 by task kworker/0:0/9
  Workqueue: events uhid_device_add_worker [uhid]
  Call Trace:
   hid_go_probe+0x3d3/0x410 [hid_lenovo_go]
   hid_device_probe+0x4a9/0x7e0 [hid]
   really_probe+0x1c3/0x690
   __driver_probe_device+0x1bc/0x380
   driver_probe_device+0x49/0x210
   __device_attach_driver+0x160/0x320
   bus_for_each_drv+0x112/0x1a0
   __device_attach+0x193/0x380
   device_initial_probe+0x78/0xa0
   bus_probe_device+0x5d/0x140
   device_add+0xd80/0x14a0
   hid_add_device+0x2b6/0x4f0 [hid]
   uhid_device_add_worker+0x3b/0x100 [uhid]

  The buggy address is located 1944 bytes to the right of
   allocated 2040-byte region [ffff8880092b4000, ffff8880092b47f8)

Followed by a GP fault when the OOB-read pointer is dereferenced to
fetch ->endpoint:

  Oops: general protection fault, probably for non-canonical address
        0xdffffc0000000003
  KASAN: null-ptr-deref in range [0x18-0x1f]
  RIP: 0010:hid_go_probe+0xef/0x410 [hid_lenovo_go]

Fix by rejecting non-USB devices at the top of probe via hid_is_usb(),
matching the pattern established for other USB-only HID drivers.
hid_is_usb() checks hdev->ll_driver == &usb_hid_driver
(drivers/hid/usbhid/hid-core.c:1356-1360), which correctly rejects
uhid devices since uhid sets ll_driver = &uhid_hid_driver
(drivers/hid/uhid.c:524). Checking hdev->bus alone is not sufficient
because UHID_CREATE2 lets userspace set bus to BUS_USB.

Reproducer (crash-only, no exploitation primitive): open /dev/uhid,
send UHID_CREATE2 with bus=BUS_USB, vendor=0x17ef and one of the
Legion Go 2 product IDs from hid_go_devices (0x61eb-0x61ee). A minimal
24-byte keyboard report descriptor is sufficient. /dev/uhid is
accessible by members of the input group on default desktop installs.

Tested-by: Derek J. Clark <derekjohn.clark@gmail.com>
Fixes: d69ccfcbc955 ("HID: hid-lenovo-go: Add Lenovo Legion Go Series HID Driver")
Fixes: a23f3497bf20 ("HID: hid-lenovo-go-s: Add Lenovo Legion Go S Series HID Driver")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Louis Clinckx <clinckx.louis@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/hid/hid-lenovo-go-s.c | 3 +++
 drivers/hid/hid-lenovo-go.c   | 3 +++
 2 files changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/hid/hid-lenovo-go-s.c b/drivers/hid/hid-lenovo-go-s.c
index 01c7bdd4f..abf477e68 100644
--- a/drivers/hid/hid-lenovo-go-s.c
+++ b/drivers/hid/hid-lenovo-go-s.c
@@ -1432,6 +1432,9 @@ static int hid_gos_probe(struct hid_device *hdev,
 {
 	int ret, ep;
 
+	if (!hid_is_usb(hdev))
+		return -EINVAL;
+
 	ret = hid_parse(hdev);
 	if (ret) {
 		hid_err(hdev, "Parse failed\n");
diff --git a/drivers/hid/hid-lenovo-go.c b/drivers/hid/hid-lenovo-go.c
index d4d26c783..3fa1fe83f 100644
--- a/drivers/hid/hid-lenovo-go.c
+++ b/drivers/hid/hid-lenovo-go.c
@@ -2419,6 +2419,9 @@ static int hid_go_probe(struct hid_device *hdev, const struct hid_device_id *id)
 {
 	int ret, ep;
 
+	if (!hid_is_usb(hdev))
+		return -EINVAL;
+
 	hdev->quirks |= HID_QUIRK_INPUT_PER_APP | HID_QUIRK_MULTI_INPUT;
 
 	ret = hid_parse(hdev);
-- 
2.54.0

